{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-14",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_14_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "La Paloma",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 245.62,
  "page_end_sec": 491.48,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.72,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 245.62,
      "end": 247.16,
      "text": "It's not likely he thought I'd die."
    },
    {
      "start": 248.02,
      "end": 250.54,
      "text": "He'd know I'd be up and around in ten or twelve hours."
    },
    {
      "start": 251.42,
      "end": 254.2,
      "text": "So maybe the answer's that he figured he could get it without"
    },
    {
      "start": 254.2,
      "end": 257.28,
      "text": "my help in that time if I was fixed so I couldn't butt in."
    },
    {
      "start": 258.04,
      "end": 258.86,
      "text": "He scowled."
    },
    {
      "start": 259.38,
      "end": 261.02,
      "text": "\"I hope to Christ he was wrong.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 261.68,
      "end": 263.2,
      "text": "His stare became less distant."
    },
    {
      "start": 264.08,
      "end": 266.06,
      "text": "\"You didn't get any word from the O'Shaughnessy?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 266.48,
      "end": 269.42,
      "text": "The girl shook her head no and asked:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 269.9,
      "end": 271.8,
      "text": "\"Has this got anything to do with her?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 272.38,
      "end": 273.08,
      "text": "\"Something.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 274.36,
      "end": 275.9,
      "text": "\"This thing he wants belongs to her?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 276.86,
      "end": 277.72,
      "text": "\"Or to the King of Spain.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 279.04,
      "end": 279.34,
      "text": "Sweetheart,"
    },
    {
      "start": 279.44,
      "end": 281.22,
      "text": "you've got an uncle who teaches history"
    },
    {
      "start": 281.22,
      "end": 282.64,
      "text": "or something over at the University?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 283.72,
      "end": 284.1,
      "text": "\"A cousin.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 284.24,
      "end": 284.52,
      "text": "Why?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 285.66,
      "end": 287.4,
      "text": "\"If we brightened his life with an alleged",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 287.44,
      "end": 290.26,
      "text": "historical secret four centuries old could we"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.26,
      "end": 291.48,
      "text": "trust him to keep it dark awhile?"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.64,
      "end": 292.98,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 293.06,
      "end": 293.48,
      "text": "yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 293.66,
      "end": 294.5,
      "text": "he's good people.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 295.18,
      "end": 295.72,
      "text": "\"Fine.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 295.94,
      "end": 297.26,
      "text": "Get your pencil and book.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 298.36,
      "end": 299.98,
      "text": "She got them and sat in her chair.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 301.088,
      "end": 303.28,
      "text": "Spade ran more cold water on his handkerchief and,"
    },
    {
      "start": 303.28,
      "end": 304.64,
      "text": "and, holding it to his temple,"
    },
    {
      "start": 304.76,
      "end": 305.82,
      "text": "stood in front of her"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.98,
      "end": 309.6,
      "text": "and dictated the story of the falcon as he had heard it from Gutman,"
    },
    {
      "start": 309.76,
      "end": 310.56,
      "text": "from Charles V's grant to"
    },
    {
      "start": 311.86,
      "end": 313.1,
      "text": "the Hospitallers up to—"
    },
    {
      "start": 313.36,
      "end": 314.52,
      "text": "but no further than—"
    },
    {
      "start": 314.7,
      "end": 315.48,
      "text": "the enameled bird's arrival in Paris at the time of"
    },
    {
      "start": 315.02,
      "end": 317.86,
      "text": "the enameled bird's arrival in Paris at the time of"
    },
    {
      "start": 317.86,
      "end": 319.02,
      "text": "the Carlist influx."
    },
    {
      "start": 319.2,
      "end": 321.56,
      "text": "He stumbled over the names of authors and"
    },
    {
      "start": 321.56,
      "end": 323.16,
      "text": "their works that Gutman had mentioned,"
    },
    {
      "start": 323.54,
      "end": 326.46,
      "text": "but managed to achieve some sort of phonetic likeness."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.16,
      "end": 328.74,
      "text": "The rest of the history he repeated"
    },
    {
      "start": 328.84,
      "end": 331.1,
      "text": "with the accuracy of a trained interviewer."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.82,
      "end": 332.5,
      "text": "When he had finished,"
    },
    {
      "start": 332.58,
      "end": 333.9,
      "text": "the girl shut her notebook and"
    },
    {
      "start": 334.06,
      "end": 335.72,
      "text": "raised a flushed smiling face to him."
    },
    {
      "start": 335.9,
      "end": 336.0,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 336.76,
      "end": 338.08,
      "text": "isn't this thrilling?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 338.4,
      "end": 339.14,
      "text": "she said."
    },
    {
      "start": 339.44,
      "end": 340.06,
      "text": "\"It's—\""
    },
    {
      "start": 340.88,
      "end": 341.86,
      "text": "\"Yes, or ridiculous.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 342.84,
      "end": 342.96,
      "text": "Now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 343.06,
      "end": 344.66,
      "text": "will you take it over and read it to your"
    },
    {
      "start": 344.66,
      "end": 346.8,
      "text": "cousin and ask him what he thinks of it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 347.82,
      "end": 349.46,
      "text": "Has he ever run across anything that"
    },
    {
      "start": 349.46,
      "end": 351.14,
      "text": "might have some connection with it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 351.7,
      "end": 352.52,
      "text": "Is it probable?"
    },
    {
      "start": 352.84,
      "end": 353.68,
      "text": "Is it"
    },
    {
      "start": 353.7,
      "end": 354.18,
      "text": "possible—"
    },
    {
      "start": 354.4,
      "end": 355.8,
      "text": "even barely possible?"
    },
    {
      "start": 356.78,
      "end": 357.62,
      "text": "Or is it the bunk?"
    },
    {
      "start": 358.62,
      "end": 360.34,
      "text": "If he wants more time to look it up,"
    },
    {
      "start": 360.42,
      "end": 360.66,
      "text": "O K,"
    },
    {
      "start": 360.86,
      "end": 361.12,
      "text": "but get"
    },
    {
      "start": 361.28,
      "end": 362.88,
      "text": "some sort of opinion out of him now."
    },
    {
      "start": 363.58,
      "end": 364.38,
      "text": "And for God's sake"
    },
    {
      "start": 364.42,
      "end": 365.94,
      "text": "make him keep it under his hat.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 366.86,
      "end": 367.64,
      "text": "\"I'll go right now,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 367.76,
      "end": 368.16,
      "text": "she said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 368.48,
      "end": 370.54,
      "text": "\"and you go see a doctor about that head.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 371.58,
      "end": 372.24,
      "text": "\"We'll have breakfast",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 372.46,
      "end": 372.78,
      "text": "first.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 373.06,
      "end": 373.16,
      "text": "\"No,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 374.08,
      "end": 375.32,
      "text": "I'll eat over in Berkeley."
    },
    {
      "start": 375.82,
      "end": 377.74,
      "text": "I can't wait to hear what Ted thinks of this.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 378.72,
      "end": 378.88,
      "text": "\"Well,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 379.14,
      "end": 379.82,
      "text": "Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 380.1,
      "end": 382.48,
      "text": "\"don't start boo-hooing if he laughs at you.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 383.648,
      "end": 385.16,
      "text": "After a leisurely breakfast at",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 385.26,
      "end": 385.62,
      "text": "the Palace,"
    },
    {
      "start": 385.8,
      "end": 387.76,
      "text": "during which he read both morning papers,"
    },
    {
      "start": 388.04,
      "end": 388.96,
      "text": "Spade went home,"
    },
    {
      "start": 389.18,
      "end": 389.8,
      "text": "shaved,"
    },
    {
      "start": 390.08,
      "end": 390.86,
      "text": "bathed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 390.88,
      "end": 391.36,
      "text": "rubbed"
    },
    {
      "start": 391.44,
      "end": 392.7,
      "text": "ice on his bruised temple,"
    },
    {
      "start": 392.86,
      "end": 394.12,
      "text": "and put on fresh clothes."
    },
    {
      "start": 394.5,
      "end": 396.44,
      "text": "He went to Brigid O'Shaughnessy's",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 396.5,
      "end": 397.54,
      "text": "apartment at the Coronet."
    },
    {
      "start": 398.24,
      "end": 399.34,
      "text": "Nobody was in the apartment.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 400.128,
      "end": 401.8,
      "text": "Nothing had been changed in it since"
    },
    {
      "start": 401.88,
      "end": 402.68,
      "text": "his last visit."
    },
    {
      "start": 403.54,
      "end": 404.97,
      "text": "He went to the Alexandria Hotel.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 405.92,
      "end": 406.98,
      "text": "Gutman was not in."
    },
    {
      "start": 407.39,
      "end": 409.12,
      "text": "None of the other occupants",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 409.12,
      "end": 410.36,
      "text": "of Gutman's suite was in."
    },
    {
      "start": 411.232,
      "end": 412.48,
      "text": "Spade learned that these other"
    },
    {
      "start": 412.48,
      "end": 414.38,
      "text": "occupants were the fat man's secretary,"
    },
    {
      "start": 414.86,
      "end": 415.36,
      "text": "Wilmer Cook,"
    },
    {
      "start": 415.6,
      "end": 416.86,
      "text": "and his daughter Rhea,"
    },
    {
      "start": 417.04,
      "end": 418.12,
      "text": "a brown-eyed fair-haired"
    },
    {
      "start": 418.18,
      "end": 418.74,
      "text": "fair-haired smallish girl of"
    },
    {
      "start": 418.78,
      "end": 420.04,
      "text": "smallish girl of seventeen whom the"
    },
    {
      "start": 420.68,
      "end": 421.18,
      "text": "whom the hotel-"
    },
    {
      "start": 421.34,
      "end": 422.56,
      "text": "staff said was beautiful."
    },
    {
      "start": 423.68,
      "end": 425.32,
      "text": "Spade was told that the Gutman party",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 425.32,
      "end": 427.08,
      "text": "had arrived at the hotel, from New"
    },
    {
      "start": 427.08,
      "end": 430.04,
      "text": "York, ten days before, and had not checked out."
    },
    {
      "start": 430.444,
      "end": 433.264,
      "text": "Spade went to the Belvedere and found the hotel-detective"
    },
    {
      "start": 433.264,
      "end": 434.664,
      "text": "eating in the hotel-café."
    },
    {
      "start": 435.4,
      "end": 436.0,
      "text": "\"Morning,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 436.14,
      "end": 436.38,
      "text": "Sam."
    },
    {
      "start": 437.54,
      "end": 438.72,
      "text": "\"Set down and bite an egg.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 439.02,
      "end": 440.16,
      "text": "The hotel-detective"
    },
    {
      "start": 440.52,
      "end": 441.68,
      "text": "stared at Spade's temple."
    },
    {
      "start": 442.38,
      "end": 442.82,
      "text": "By God,"
    },
    {
      "start": 442.98,
      "end": 444.34,
      "text": "somebody maced you plenty."
    },
    {
      "start": 445.04,
      "end": 445.74,
      "text": "\"Thanks,"
    },
    {
      "start": 445.9,
      "end": 446.6,
      "text": "I've had mine,"
    },
    {
      "start": 446.94,
      "end": 448.38,
      "text": "Spade said as"
    },
    {
      "start": 448.38,
      "end": 450.48,
      "text": "he sat down, and then, referring to his temple:"
    },
    {
      "start": 451.28,
      "end": 452.6,
      "text": "\"It looks worse than it is."
    },
    {
      "start": 452.78,
      "end": 454.5,
      "text": "How's my Cairo's conduct?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 455.34,
      "end": 457.74,
      "text": "\"He went out not more than half an hour behind",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 457.74,
      "end": 460.14,
      "text": "you yesterday and I ain't seen him since."
    },
    {
      "start": 460.42,
      "end": 461.24,
      "text": "He didn't"
    },
    {
      "start": 461.26,
      "end": 462.54,
      "text": "sleep here again last night.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 463.58,
      "end": 464.76,
      "text": "\"He's getting bad habits.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 465.22,
      "end": 465.92,
      "text": "\"Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 466.2,
      "end": 468.16,
      "text": "a fellow like that alone in a big"
    },
    {
      "start": 468.2,
      "end": 468.54,
      "text": "city."
    },
    {
      "start": 469.34,
      "end": 470.56,
      "text": "Who put the slug to you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 470.64,
      "end": 470.82,
      "text": "Sam?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 472.06,
      "end": 472.92,
      "text": "\"It wasn't Cairo.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 473.14,
      "end": 475.08,
      "text": "Spade looked attentively at the small"
    },
    {
      "start": 475.18,
      "end": 476.74,
      "text": "silver dome covering Luke's toast."
    },
    {
      "start": 477.984,
      "end": 480.66,
      "text": "\"How's chances of giving his room a casing while he's out?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 481.56,
      "end": 482.0,
      "text": "\"Can do.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 482.72,
      "end": 485.48,
      "text": "You know I'm willing to go all the way with you all the time.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 486.592,
      "end": 487.82,
      "text": "Luke pushed his coffee back,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 488.16,
      "end": 489.56,
      "text": "put his elbows on the table,"
    },
    {
      "start": 489.62,
      "end": 491.48,
      "text": "and screwed up his eyes at Spade."
    }
  ],
  "corrected": "claude"
}